cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of photometric stereo, which is a computer vision technique used to recover the shape and reflectance of a surface from multiple images taken under different lighting conditions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and numerical methods, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the use of spherical harmonics and variational methods indicates that it could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
